OL,3,CPoliticians in Wales to vote on
OL,4,Cassisted dying services on the NHS
OL,6,FPoliticians in Wales will vote on
OL,7,Fwhether they agree the country should
OL,8,Fhave powers to introduce assisted
OL,9,Fdying services on the NHS, if a
OL,10,Flandmark law passes in Westminster.
OL,12,FMembers of the Senedd will be voting
OL,13,Fon the issue on Tuesday, 24 February.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G1/8
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1771963515
OL,3,CPoliticians in Wales to vote on
OL,4,Cassisted dying services on the NHS
OL,6,FIt's a debate and vote on the
OL,7,Ftechnicalities of where decision-
OL,8,Fmaking should lie when it comes to
OL,9,Fintroducing such a service, not on the
OL,10,Fprinciple of assisted dying, but a
OL,11,Fmajority of the current Senedd has
OL,12,Fexpressed opposition to that
OL,13,Fprinciple, most recently in a vote in
OL,14,FOctober 2024.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/8
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1771963515
OL,3,CPoliticians in Wales to vote on
OL,4,Cassisted dying services on the NHS
OL,6,FThis week's Senedd vote also won't
OL,7,Fmake any difference to whether or not
OL,8,Fassisted dying is legalised. Powers to
OL,9,Fchange the law related to suicide are
OL,10,Fnot devolved to Cardiff, so should the
OL,11,FUK Parliament legislation pass, it
OL,12,Fwould still become legal in both Wales
OL,13,Fand England.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/8
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1771963515
OL,3,CPoliticians in Wales to vote on
OL,4,Cassisted dying services on the NHS
OL,6,FBut there are a lot of issues yet to
OL,7,Fbe resolved in Westminster. The
OL,8,FTerminally Ill Adults (End of Life)
OL,9,FBill is currently in the House of
OL,10,FLords, where supporters have raised
OL,11,Fconcerns that the high volume of
OL,12,Famendments could mean the legislation
OL,13,Fdoes not pass.
OL,15,FThe UK Parliament could decide to
OL,16,Fignore the Senedd vote, but the
OL,17,Fbackers of the legislation have said
OL,18,Fthey would change the bill to redact
OL,19,Fparts relating to Wales should MSs
OL,20,Fvote against it.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/8
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1771963515
OL,3,CPoliticians in Wales to vote on
OL,4,Cassisted dying services on the NHS
OL,6,FIf the Senedd refuses to give consent
OL,7,Fto the England and Wales bill, it
OL,8,Fcould mean that services are still
OL,9,Favailable in Wales but not on the NHS.
OL,11,FThat's because health is devolved, so
OL,12,Fthe implementation of any assisted
OL,13,Fdying service would be carried out
OL,14,Fthrough the Welsh NHS which is
OL,15,Fcontrolled by the Welsh Government and
OL,16,Fultimately answerable to the Senedd
OL,17,Fitself.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G5/8
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1771963515
OL,3,CPoliticians in Wales to vote on
OL,4,Cassisted dying services on the NHS
OL,6,FIn a vote in October 2024 on the
OL,7,Fprinciple of assisted dying, Senedd
OL,8,Fmembers including First Minister
OL,9,FEluned Morgan and Health Secretary
OL,10,FJeremy Miles voted against it, which
OL,11,Fcould indicate that MSs could vote to
OL,12,Fblock it on Tuesday.
OL,14,FThat in turn raises the prospect of
OL,15,Fassisted dying being legalised here in
OL,16,FWales but Welsh doctors prohibited
OL,17,Ffrom providing the service on the NHS.
OL,18,FIt wouldn't prevent charities or
OL,19,Fprivate sector companies offering the
OL,20,Fservice.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G6/8
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1771963515
OL,3,CPoliticians in Wales to vote on
OL,4,Cassisted dying services on the NHS
OL,6,FThis decision is a personal and
OL,7,Femotional one, mixing questions of
OL,8,Fpower and principle with a lot of
OL,9,Funcertainty about what is the right
OL,10,Fway to proceed.
OL,12,FSome of those arguing for Senedd
OL,13,Fmembers to vote 'no' are supporters of
OL,14,Fthe principle of assisted dying, but
OL,15,Fcritics of the legislation.
OL,17,FSimilarly, some of those arguing for a
OL,18,F'yes' vote are opponents of assisted
OL,19,Fdying, but keen to see decision-making
OL,20,Fand regulation lie with politicians in
OL,21,FCardiff, not London.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G7/8
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46308
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1771963515
OL,3,CPoliticians in Wales to vote on
OL,4,Cassisted dying services on the NHS
OL,6,FSuch votes are usually "conscience"
OL,7,Fvotes, where Senedd members don't vote
OL,8,Falong party lines. That won't make it
OL,9,Fany easier; it will make Tuesday's
OL,10,Fdecision difficult and the debate
OL,11,Fpersonal and emotional.
OL,26,@nD@XOUnD@cO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G8/8
